R&D Experiment: Client-side Rendering — Next.js

Exploring pre-rendering vs. client-side rendering — this site is client-side rendered with Next.js. HTML generated at build time for faster initial loads and better SEO. Client-side rendering, by contrast, builds the UI in the browser using JavaScript after the initial load.
